### Example 3: Responsive Grid Gallery

```jsx
function Gallery({ images }) {
  return (
    <div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold mb-8">Photo Gallery</h1>

      <div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        {images.map((image, index) => (
          <div
            key={index}
            className="
              group relative aspect-square overflow-hidden rounded-lg
              cursor-pointer transition-transform hover:scale-105
            "
          >
            <img
              src={image.src}
              alt={image.alt}
              className="w-full h-full object-cover"
            />
            <div className="
              absolute inset-0 bg-black/60 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100
              transition-opacity flex items-center justify-center
            ">
              <div className="text-white text-center p-4">
                <h3 className="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">{image.title}</h3>
                <p className="text-sm">{image.description}</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Best Practices

1. **Use Semantic Class Names**: Combine Tailwind with component-based architecture
2. **Leverage @apply**: Extract repeated patterns into custom CSS classes
3. **Mobile-First**: Always start with mobile design and scale up
4. **Consistent Spacing**: Use the spacing scale (4, 8, 16, 24, 32, etc.)
5. **Color Palette**: Define custom colors in config, use semantic names
6. **Responsive Typography**: Use responsive font sizes and line heights
7. **Performance**: Optimize builds with PurgeCSS and minimize custom CSS
8. **Accessibility**: Combine with proper semantic HTML and ARIA attributes
9. **Dark Mode**: Plan for dark mode from the start
10. **Component Library**: Build reusable components with class-variance-authority
